# Base URL of the Go API. Leave EMPTY in both local dev and production.
# - Local dev: Vite proxies /api to :8080 (see vite.config.ts).
# - Production: vercel.json rewrites /api/* to the Render service, keeping API
#   calls same-origin so the SameSite=Lax session cookie is sent. Pointing this
#   at a cross-origin Render URL would drop the cookie and silently break auth.
# The Vercel Edge Middleware (apps/web/middleware.ts) falls back to the request
# origin when this is empty, so it also routes through the same-origin proxy.
VITE_API_URL=
